for Windows user
1. install python 2.7
2. install jinja2
    open "cmd" , pip install jinja2
3. modify LINE 27 of "<Python27>\Lib\site-packages\jinja2\loaders.py"
  from
    for piece in template.split('/'):
  to
    for piece in template.split(os.sep):
4. install git
5. entering "web_cooking" folder
  cd <web_cooking>
6. generate AngularJs App
  Cook\cook.py materials food\simple menu\commonSimple.menu ALL
7. run on http-server
  Cook\cook.py materials food\simple menu\commonSimple.menu RUN

for Ubuntu/Debian user
1. install python 2.7
  apt-get install python2.7
2. install jinja2
  apt-get install python-jinja2
3. install nodejs
  apt-get install nodejs  
4. install git
  apt-get install git
5. entering "web_cooking" folder
  cd <web_cooking>
6. generate AngularJs App
  Cook/cook.py materials food/simple menu/commonSimple.menu ALL
7. run on http-server
  Cook/cook.py materials food/simple menu/commonSimple.menu RUN
